# Repository Layer

This project uses **module services** for data access (no separate `repositories/` folder yet). Treat service Prisma calls as the data layer until repositories are introduced.

## When adding repositories

Repositories must:

- Only communicate with Prisma
- Never contain business logic, HTTP, or auth checks
- Return domain-shaped data, not Express types
- Use `select` to fetch only required fields

```typescript
// ✅ Repository
async findByEmail(email: string) {
  return prisma.user.findUnique({
    where: { email },
    select: { id: true, email: true, passwordHash: true, status: true },
  });
}

// ❌ Repository with business logic
async login(email: string, password: string) { ... }
```

## Services call repositories

When refactored: `controller → service → repository → Prisma`. Until then, keep Prisma in services but isolated in private methods or clear sections.

Never fetch unnecessary fields or deep relation trees by default.
